  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Confronting Climate Change in the Peruvian Andes through Renewable Energy and Community Water Initiatives</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improve living conditions for rural communities through the climate change mitigation and adaptation measures of renewable energy and efficient water use. Objective 1: 95 families and 65 schoolchildren have improved living conditions and mitigate climate change impacts through the use of clean, renewable energy in their homes and schools. 
 50 families and 65 schoolchildren have increased access to clean, treated water in order to better adapt to the effects of climate change.  
 140 rural women have strengthened their ability to adapt to climate change, through better information, skills development, and improved inter-family skills and organization.
 LWR and ITDG-Practical Solutions along with the beneficiaries of the project have identified best practices and principle limitations of the approach; by designing and applying a methodology to evaluated the impacts of the project.</narrative>
  </description>
